    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-10-07T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-10-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="639"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d639">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795A.5/10–750: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Norway</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Snow</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Oslo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-10-07T12:00:00+01:00"
                            >October 7, 1950—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 7—10:35 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>357. Norwegian Foreign Office has now received from its representative at Peiping
                    report similar to that contained <gloss target="#t_Depcirtel1">Depcirtel</gloss>
                    9, October 5, 11 a. m., except for two variations: (1) No reference made to
                    abstention from action if <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> troops crossed
                    Parallel; and (2) Chinese Communist Government would not recognize any
                    settlement of Korean problem in which Peiping Government did not
                    participate.</p>
                <p>Norwegian Foreign Office has no indications Soviet intentions re Korea.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Snow</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
